data.chText: 裸体的；裸露的；不穿衣服的
他们经常赤身裸体地在房子里走来走去。
data.enText: They often wandered around the house stark naked (= completely naked) .

data.chText: 他们发现他身体半裸，流着血，快不行了。
data.enText: They found him half naked and bleeding to death.
Mice are born naked (= without fur) .

data.chText: 直白的；露骨的；毫不掩饰的

data.enText: unable to protect yourself from being harmed, criticized, etc.

data.chText: 经历了这场磨难之后，他仍然感到无法自卫，而且筋疲力尽。
data.enText: He still felt naked and drained after his ordeal.
the normal power of your eyes without the help of an instrument

data.chText: 这颗行星肉眼就能看得见。
data.enText: The planet should be visible with/to the naked eye .

data.chText: 以上两词均含裸露、未穿衣服之义，常与下列名词连用：
data.enText: Both these words can be used to mean ‘not covered with clothes’ and are frequently used with the following nouns.

data.chText: naked较常用以表示赤身裸体，而bare通常指身体某部位裸露着。
data.enText: Naked is more often used to describe a person or their body and bare usually describes a part of the body.

data.chText: bare亦可用以描述其他没有遮盖或光秃的东西：
data.enText: Bare can also describe other things with nothing on them.
Naked can mean ‘without a protective covering’.

data.chText: naked可用以表示赤裸裸、无掩饰的强烈感情：
data.enText: Naked can be used to talk about strong feelings that are not hidden.

ex.chText: 他们发现尸体半裸着躺在草丛中。
ex.enText: They found the body lying half naked in the grass.

ex.chText: 孩子们光着身子跑过花园。
ex.enText: The children ran naked through the garden.

ex.chText: 那两只小老鼠还没长毛，眼睛也尚未睁开。
ex.enText: Those two little mice were naked and blind.

synonyms.bx: 指人没有穿衣服的，也指动物尚未长出皮毛或羽毛的。

ex.enText: The child was bare to the waist.

ex.chText: 我光脚踩在沙滩上，感到热乎乎的。
ex.enText: The sand was warm under my bare feet.

ex.chText: 泥土被洪水冲走，露出光秃秃的岩石。
ex.enText: The soil was washed away by the flood, exposing bare rock.

ex.chText: 那棵树的很多树枝都光秃秃的。
ex.enText: Many branches of the tree are bare.

synonyms.bx: 多指身体没有衣服覆盖的，也指土地荒芜的或树木没有叶子的。

d: 赤裸的，裸露的；光秃秃的

synonyms.bx: 指人体全裸的，尤用于形容模特儿，比 naked 委婉。

ex.chText: 他脱衣服花了很长时间。
我不知道自己裸体是什么样。
ex.enText: I don't know what I look like when I'm undressed.

synonyms.bx: 指人未穿任何衣服的，只作表语。

tr: devoid of elaboration or diminution or concealment
example: you may kill someone someday with your raw power

tr: having no protecting or concealing cover
(of the eye or ear e.g.) without the aid of an optical or acoustical device or instrument

value.def: Someone who is naked is not wearing any clothes.

example.ex: Her naked body was found wrapped in a sheet in a field...
example.tran: 在田里发现了她的尸体，全身赤裸，裹在一条床单里。

example.ex: The hot paving stones scorched my naked feet...
example.tran: 烫人的铺路石灼烤着我的一双赤脚。

example.ex: He stood naked in front of me.
example.tran: 他赤身裸体地站在我面前。

gramarinfo.label: ADJ n, ADJ after v, v-link ADJ

example.ex: He had pulled the blanket over his body to hide his nakedness.
example.tran: 他把毛毯扯过来裹住自己赤裸的身体。

value.def: If an animal or part of an animal is naked, it has no fur or feathers on it.

example.ex: The nest contained eight little mice that were naked and blind.
example.tran: 窝里有8只还没长毛、眼睛尚未睁开的小老鼠。

value.tran: (动物)没有皮毛的，没有羽毛的

value.def: If you say that someone is naked or feels naked, you mean they are powerless or have no way of protecting themselves.

example.ex: If the reports are accurate, the deal leaves the authorities and the President virtually naked.
example.tran: 如果报道属实，此交易的确使当局和总统猝不及防。

example.ex: ...Bevan's appeal against going 'naked into the conference chamber'.
example.tran: 贝文“不要毫无准备地走进会议室”的呼吁

gramarinfo.label: ADJ after v, v-link ADJ, ADJ n

value.def: You can describe an object as naked when it does not have its normal covering.

example.ex: ...a naked bulb dangling in a bare room...
example.tran: 空荡荡的房间里吊着的一只没有灯罩的灯泡

example.ex: The water was heated by a naked gas flame.
example.tran: 水是用燃气明火加热的。

value.def: Naked emotions are easy to recognize, because they are very strongly felt.

example.ex: The naked hatred in the woman's face shocked me...
example.tran: 那位女士一脸毫不掩饰的憎恨让我震惊。

example.ex: There had been naked misery in her voice when she'd  spoken about the letter.
example.tran: 她说起那封信时，声音里流露出明显的痛苦。

example.ex: She was embarrassed at showing her fear so nakedly.
example.tran: 她对于如此直接地表露了自己的恐惧感到尴尬不已。

value.def: You can use naked to describe unpleasant or violent actions and behaviour which are not disguised or hidden in any way.

example.ex: Naked aggression and an attempt to change frontiers by force could not go unchallenged.
example.tran: 公然的侵略和企图用武力改变边界的行径是不能置之不理的。

example.ex: ...violence and the naked pursuit of power.
example.tran: 暴力以及对权力赤裸裸的追求

value.def: If you say that something cannot be seen by the naked eye, you mean that it cannot be seen without the help of equipment such as a telescope or microscope.

example.ex: The worms cannot be seen by the naked eye...
example.tran: 这些虫子用肉眼看不见。

example.ex: The planet Mars will be visible to the naked eye all week...
example.tran: 整周都可以用肉眼观察到火星。

example.ex: There's  so much going on that you can't see with the naked eye.
example.tran: 有很多正在发生的事情肉眼是无法察觉的。
